3.  Web Administrator and Programmers (36 person-months in total) 

9.  The consultants will help the ARIC lead economist to expand, improve, and operate the 
ARIC website, and the OREI website and intranet. Under the supervision of ADB staff and the 
ARIC lead economist, the consultants will: 
(i)  design  and  develop  improved  navigational  tools  using  state-of-the-art 
technologies to improve user access across various content areas of the website; 
(ii)  build and maintain efficient content management systems to track and manage 
content, including text and graphics published on the website; 
(iii)  build highly interactive interfaces, a geo-data mapper, and charting components 
for  the macroeconomic  and financial  indicators  database  and  the  integration 
indicators database, and build a comparative toolkit for the free trade agreements 
database; 
(iv)  develop a multimedia facility to manage image galleries, podcasts, and video 
feeds; 
(v)  implement a system to track website statistics on user hits and visits; 
(vi)  conceptualize and execute designs for new uploads, and suggest modifications 
in page design; 
(vii)  analyze program specifications, design and implement programs to generate 
links and webpages, and test and debug the programs; 
(viii)  maintain or modify programs to revise and update the content of the new website; 
(ix)  develop new concepts to simplify website updating procedures; 
(x)  update and check the entire database for errors, and manage the file structure of 
the entire website; 
(xi)  upload daily updates on the development, intranet, and global websites; 
(xii)  prepare technical documentation for the new and expanded ARIC website; 
(xiii)  conceptualize and develop CD brochures and portable database applications; 
(xiv)  conduct usability testing to evaluate and measure the website’s ease of use; and 
(xv)  provide other information technology (IT) support as may be requested by the 
lead economist and/or ADB staff. 

4.  Multimedia Designer and Developer (18 person-months) 

10.  The consultant will help the ARIC lead economist expand, improve, and operate the 
ARIC  website  by  undertaking  graphic  design  work  on  ARIC’s  websites  and  other  related 
subsites. Under the supervision of ADB staff and the ARIC lead economist, the consultant will: 
(i)  conceptualize designs and develop front-end templates for ARIC websites and 
other related subsites; 
(ii)  manage and update static content for ARIC websites and related subsites; 
(iii)  conceptualize and execute specified design including icons and thumbnails of 
new web pages and additional subsites; 
(iv)  carry out other tasks related to web graphic design as assigned by ADB staff;

14  Appendix 3 


13.  Under the supervision of the ARIC lead economist, the consultant will: 
(i)  coordinate the teams’ schedules, meetings, and mission requirements; 
(ii)  assist the team with all logistics required during meetings, conferences, and 
workshops, and manage all administrative procedures; 
(iii)  maintain and organize ARIC files, reports, and other documents; 
(iv)  manage the contact database and other databases for the team; 
(v)  assist in collecting and formatting online data and references; 
(vi)  prepare a monthly economic calendar for use by ARIC’s economic analysts; 
(vii)  monitor the team’s business procedures and systems including staff attendance; 
(viii)  serve as the supply custodian for the ARIC team; 
(ix)  provide secretarial support and assistance if and when necessary; and 
(x)  undertake other functions as may be assigned by the lead economist and/or ADB 
staff. 

C.  Resource People (1 person-month) 

14.  Consultants will be engaged as resource people for the seminar series on RCI. These 
consultants  are  expected  to  be  distinguished  international  experts  specializing  in  regional 
cooperation and integration issues, or policy makers who are considered champions of Asian 
integration. The resource people will: 
(i)  conduct presentations on the topics assigned to them; and  
(ii)  moderate and facilitate active discussion and exchanges of ideas among the 
participants, as well as with other resource people.
